casebody.data:
Christopher T. DEAN, Appellant,
v.
STATE of Florida, Appellee. No. 4D14-681 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Fourth District. [January 10, 2018] Carey Haughwout, Public Defender, and Paul E. Petillo, Assistant Public Defender, West Palm Beach, for appellant. Pamela Jo Bondi, Attorney General, Tallahassee, and Melanie Dale Surber, Assistant Attorney General, West Palm Beach, for appellee.

ON REMAND FROM THE SUPREME COURT

Per Curiam.

Pursuant to the mandate from the Supreme Court in Dean v. State , 230 So.3d 420 (Fla. 2017), we affirm appellant's convictions and remand for resentencing.

Gross, Damoorgian and Klingensmith, JJ., concur.
